The paper deals with learning-based hashing methods for nearest neighbor retrieval, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR). The paper also proposes an optimization method using stochastic gradient descent, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and optimization (LG). The paper uses image retrieval benchmarks, which is a common application in multimedia (MM). Finally, the paper addresses the challenge of binary codes for indexed data, which is a common problem in data structures (DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, and cs.DS.
